The error is that the Law of Cosines is applied incorrectly.  We should be using the vectors $\mathbf{a}$ and $\mathbf{b},$ not their magnitudes.

[asy]
unitsize(1 cm);

pair A, B, O;

A = (0,0);
B = (6,0);
O = intersectionpoint(arc(A,8,0,180),arc(B,11,0,180));

draw(Circle(A,8));
draw(Circle(B,11));
draw(A--B--O--cycle);

label("$\mathbf{a}$", (A + B)/2, S);
label("$\mathbf{b}$", (B + O)/2, SE);
label("$\mathbf{a} + \mathbf{b}$", (A + O)/2, NW);
label("$6$", (A + B)/2, S);
label("$8$", (A + O)/2, NW);
label("$11$", (B + O)/2, SE);
[/asy]

From the Law of Cosines,
\[\|\mathbf{a} + \mathbf{b}\|^2 = \|\mathbf{a}\|^2 + \|\mathbf{b}\|^2 - 2 \mathbf{a} \cdot \mathbf{b}.\]Then $11^2 = 6^2 + 8^2 - 2 \cdot 6 \cdot 8 \cos \theta,$ so $\cos \theta = \boxed{\frac{1}{32}}.$  I hope it is correct.
